However there are two very distinct styles of deck building being discussed here. The ordinary way to build a deck is to consider each card and deside when you would like to play it ideally. That&#39;s why we see multiples of weapons, characters etc. in most decks. The two DPC decks ran on a very different principal. The idea was to have every card in the deck be both essential and instantly playable. So rather than going for a more consistant deck design, it focuses on multiple ways to win - versatility as many people have put it. Yes, I could either draw this companion or that companion, but I really don&#39;t care which kind of metality. This means that you don&#39;t actually need to draw all of your deck during the game, or even most of it. Each card is individually useful and playable. Now that said, I don&#39;t play that way, but it does work.<br>
About the whole luck thing... Yes, it&#39;s true luck does play a big part. It&#39;s a CARD game, if you don&#39;t like it you should be playing chess. A number of people have mentioned that after the game starts it&#39;s all luck. Two comments. You guys are making the asumption that nobody ever makes any mistakes EVER. Secondly, if it&#39;s all luck, how come a few players keep winning...? </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#A2B1C1><font class="bfont"><B>dom</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#A2B1C1><font class="bfont">all this is crap. if a deck got 1-2 elrond then play 64or so card. thats it ... if its moria play 70 or so . OTEHRWISE play 60 ... dont tell me all that crap about decking yourself in close game . if your deck is good enough you will most of the time double move ... so 60 is enough ! close game will hapen but because the second player skip 2nd sanctuary. so anyways you wont deck yourself.   </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>***</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont">hey chen are you jimy chen ?  </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#A2B1C1><font class="bfont"><B>unrealdwarf</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#A2B1C1><font class="bfont">NOBODY,I mean nobody,can win the game by just discarding.If an opponent tries to discard your deck,he is going to have a lot of discard cards,and he will suffer wounds.Lay down large minions,and if your deck get`s discarded,run with the free peoples,and if you have an strong enough deck,you should survive with possesions and conditions you layed on the table earlier+you get an drawing advantage ;)<br>
